.TH SORTIE 1 "March 2026" "sortie dev" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sortie \- intelligent file dispatcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sortie
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sortie
is a rule\-based file routing tool that watches directories (like ~/Downloads
and ~/Desktop) and automatically moves, copies, renames, compresses, or deletes
files based on configurable rules.
.PP
Configuration uses a hybrid approach: a central config file at
.I ~/.config/sortie/config.yaml
defines watched directories and global rules, while optional per\-directory
.I .sortie.yaml
files add or override rules for specific directories. Per\-directory rules
take precedence over global rules (first\-match\-wins evaluation).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan \fR[\fIdirectory...\fR]
Scan one or more directories (or all configured directories) and apply matching
rules. Use \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR to preview without executing.
.TP
.B watch
Watch all configured directories for new files in real time. Runs as a
foreground daemon with configurable debounce. Exits cleanly on SIGINT/SIGTERM.
.TP
.B history
Show recent dispatch actions. Use \fB\-n\fR or \fB\-\-limit\fR to control output.
.TP
.B undo \fR[\fIid\fR]
Reverse the most recent action, or a specific action by ID. Use \fB\-\-last N\fR
to undo the last N actions.
.TP
.B rules
List all configured rules (global and per\-directory).
.TP
.B rules test \fR\fIfile\fR
Show which rule would match a given file.
.TP
.B config
Show the resolved configuration.
.TP
.B config init
Create a starter config file with commented examples.
.TP
.B config path
Print the config file path.
.TP
.B status
Check if the watcher daemon is running, show watched directories and rule counts.
.TP
.B trash
List files in the trash directory.
.TP
.B trash purge
Permanently delete all files in trash.
.TP
.B man
Display this manual page.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIpath\fR
Config file path. Default: \fI~/.config/sortie/config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output.
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SS "scan flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Preview actions without executing.
.SS "watch flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Log what would happen without executing.
.TP
.BR \-\-debounce " " \fIduration\fR
Debounce period for file events. Default: 500ms.
.SS "history flags"
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-limit " " \fIN\fR
Maximum number of records to show. Default: 20.
.SS "undo flags"
.TP
.BR \-\-last " " \fIN\fR
Number of recent actions to undo. Default: 1.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.SS "Central Config"
Located at \fI~/.config/sortie/config.yaml\fR. Run \fBsortie config init\fR to
generate a starter file.
.PP
.nf
directories:
  \- path: ~/Downloads
    recursive: false

rules:
  \- name: images\-to\-photos
    match:
      extensions: [.jpg, .jpeg, .png, .heic]
    action:
      type: move
      dest: ~/Pictures/Sorted/{{.Year}}/{{.Month}}
.fi
.SS "Per\-Directory Config"
Place a \fI.sortie.yaml\fR file in any watched directory. These rules are
evaluated before global rules for that directory.
.PP
.nf
rules:
  \- name: pdfs\-to\-documents
    match:
      extensions: [.pdf]
    action:
      type: move
      dest: ~/Documents/PDFs
.fi
.SS "Match Conditions"
All specified conditions use AND logic.
.TP
.B extensions
List of file extensions (e.g., [.jpg, .png]).
.TP
.B glob
Filename glob pattern (e.g., "Screenshot*").
.TP
.B regex
Regular expression matched against filename.
.TP
.B min_size\fR, \fBmax_size
File size thresholds (e.g., "500MB", "1GB").
.TP
.B min_age\fR, \fBmax_age
File age thresholds (e.g., "30d", "2h").
.TP
.B mime_type
MIME type prefix match (e.g., "image/", "application/pdf").
.SS "Action Types"
.TP
.B move
Move the file to the destination.
.TP
.B copy
Copy the file to the destination.
.TP
.B rename
Rename the file using a template.
.TP
.B delete
Move the file to the trash directory (~/.config/sortie/trash/).
.TP
.B compress
Gzip the file and remove the original.
.SS "Template Variables"
Destination paths support Go template syntax:
.TP
.B {{.Name}}
Filename without extension.
.TP
.B {{.Ext}}
Extension including dot.
.TP
.B {{.Year}}\fR, \fB{{.Month}}\fR, \fB{{.Day}}
From file modification time.
.TP
.B {{.Date}}
YYYY\-MM\-DD format.
.TP
.B {{.Time}}
HH\-MM\-SS format.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/config.yaml
Central configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/history.json
Action history (JSON Lines format).
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/trash/
Trash directory for deleted files.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/logs/
Log directory for watch mode.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sortie/sortie.pid
PID file written by the watcher daemon.
.TP
.I .sortie.yaml
Per\-directory rule overrides.
.SH EXAMPLES
Initialize configuration:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie config init
.fi
.PP
Preview what would happen in ~/Downloads:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie scan ~/Downloads \-\-dry\-run
.fi
.PP
Run the scan for real:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie scan
.fi
.PP
Start watching in real time:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie watch
.fi
.PP
Check which rule matches a file:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie rules test ~/Downloads/report.pdf
.fi
.PP
Undo the last 3 actions:
.PP
.nf
$ sortie undo \-\-last 3
.fi
.SH RUNNING AS A SERVICE
On macOS, sortie can run as a launchd user agent to watch directories
automatically at login.
.PP
Install the service:
.PP
.nf
$ make install\-launchd
.fi
.PP
This creates a plist at
.I ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist
that starts
.B sortie watch
at login. Logs go to
.IR ~/.config/sortie/logs/sortie.log .
.PP
Manage the service:
.PP
.nf
# Stop
$ launchctl unload ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist

# Start
$ launchctl load ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.msjurset.sortie.plist

# Uninstall
$ make uninstall\-launchd
.fi
